content: Great app. It's amazing how difficult it is to do a metar app correctly. METAM was my go-to for years, but it's no longer supported. This app is very good. The customizable Zulu clock is perfect. The layout is great. Dark mode is great. The only thing I wish it had is D-ATIS. He makes another app for that, but it'd be nice to have it in this one. Overall great product. Thanks!

Best airport wx ap I have ever used. As an airline pilot I've used several. Pd the $1.58 for the Pro version to support the product. (The pro features are OK. Nothing special for my needs.) I really like the AP!!
replyContent: Thank you for the review!  As a fellow airline pilot I hope I've included features my peers enjoy using.  Please let me know if you have any other suggestions or comments! -Steve

content: Very good app. Have the Pro version. Like the features, customizable. Surely recommend it.
replyContent: Thanks Roberto, and please pass along any suggestions for new features!

content: Please allow for arbitrary sorting. I like to sort airports by region to get a picture of area weather.
replyContent: Hi Rod!  I am planning on adding this feature soon in an update. Thanks!

content: Tried Avia first, wouldn't let me search for airports using ICAO identifiers. But would find local airports. Spent the $3.75 to unlock all of the features, still couldn't search for what I was looking for. This is perfect, with the $.99 to upgrade to Pro for the color coded precipitation. If you want an easy to use, no frills way of checking METAR/TAF info, this is for you.
replyContent: Thank you so much for your kind words! I am always looking to add new features that my users would find useful, so if you have any suggestions please send me an email. I really enjoy making Windsock, so thank you again and I'm happy you find it useful!
